<br>
Of course, many MANY of the kanji are the same.<br>
The writing system of Japan is an importation and adaptation from China's writing system.<br>
(Japan had no writing until the Chinese system came to Japan.)<br>
<br>
A typical Kanji in Japanese will have a Japanese pronunciation AND a Chinese-style pronunciation, so even the SOUNDS of the 2 languages will have similarities.<br>
<br>
For example, the kanji for &quot;big&quot; is pronounced &quot;DAI&quot; in Japanese, from the Chinese &quot;Da&quot;.<br>
<br>
